original_text: So there are two issues here: 1) The lag: the number of deaths _reported_ on a day won't match the number who _died_ on that day. It takes time to record a death. 2) The gaps: people are dying of Covid outside hospitals (e.g. in care homes) without being tested.

original_text: The "daily deaths" will eventually catch up with the lag. When case numbers finally begin to fall, reported daily figure will be _higher_ than the number of actual deaths on a particular day. For now we're late reporting an increase; eventually we'll be late reporting a fall.
